     |                                                                     |
     |                                                                     |
     |  Army Men: Sarge's Heroes debuts at long last on the Sega           |
     |  Dreamcast! Capturing the action and intrigue created by 3DO for    |
     |  the Nintendo 64 and other platforms, Amy Men: Sarge's Heroes is    |
     |  a two-fisted non-stop firefight with firepower and attitude to     |
     |  match.                                                             |
     |                                                                     |
     |   The Army Men franchise pits the good Green plastic army men,      |
     |  honchoed by the square-jawed and stalwart Sarge, against the evil  |
     |  Tan army men, led by the malevolent General Plastro. In Sarge's    |
     |  Heroes, players take on the role of Sarge as he rescues his        | 
     |  captive commandos and the Colonel's daughter Vikki, undertaking    | 
     |  16 separate missions to get his buddies back and save the world.   |
     |  A variety of powerful weaponry abounds as Sarge must use his brain | 
     |  and brawn to overpower the enemy. In multi-player, up to four      |
     |  players can wage war against each other in deathmatch mode.        |
     |                                                                     |
     |  The gameplay is a traditional 3rd-person removed adventure game    |
     |  perspective, following your hero as he wages war. The game is      |
     |  mission-based with several objectives on each level. Strategic     |
     |  and guerilla tactics are required for success in a war where the   |
     |  odds are overwhelmingly stacked against Sarge.                     |
